main event: An observer reported seeing an unidentified aerial object near Kensington, Maryland on February 20, 1967 at 6:12 PM.
interesting points: The object appeared as a light unlike those of a plane, with red and white lights, and was traveling in a southwest-bound direction.
The object was observed for about 10 minutes.
The observer stated that the object appeared brighter than the brightest stars.
The object was described as shiny and silver-white in color.
The observer estimated the size of the object to be between 1/4 to 1/2 the size of a matchstick held at arm's length.
witnesses: 1 observer, a college graduate in astronomy
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
